    <note>Yang(2) Jian [12367] The second son of Jun [12365]. He served in the administration of the Western Wei. His first three sons did not hold office and may have died young. The fourth son, Wenen's (not in dataset) only son Anren's (not in dataset) (ancestor of the Mianzhu Yang(2)) and fifth son, Wenwei [22571], had many descendants. Anren's descendants included Hubu shangshu and other high central governmental officials, but no zaixiang. Jun's third son, Kuan's [22509] descendants included a zaixiang of Tang Wuzong. XTS, 71B.</note>
